               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra (only in Text I); name of the King, of the donor and of the scribe; incipits and headings of the texts; numbers, the word mǝʿǝraf and titles of each chapter; the names of the Evangelists and lines in the “Canon Tables”;  the word qämär (Text 1); a few lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of each Gospel; elements of the punctuation signs and numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Concerning the traditional introductive texts of the Gospel, s. R. ZUURMOND, Novum Testamentum Aethiopice: the Synoptic Gospels, Part I: General Introduction, Part II: Edition of the Gospel of Mark, Stuttgart 1989 (AeF 27), 1-31.</note>
                     <note>- In Text I, on fol. 2v, the “Statement about the Eusebian sections” ends with a short note on the symbols of the four Evangelists.</note>
                     <note>In the “List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Matthew, concerning the Ethiopian numerals, there are the following mistakes:</note>
                     <note>after ፲፰, ፲፭ ፲፮ ፲፯ are used also for the tutili noo. 19-21; for the tituli 22-25 any numeral is used; from the numeral 26 on, the numeration starts from ፲፰. The last numeral is 60 instead of 69 and written in the form ፶፲.</note>
                     <note>- Each “Bǝsrat” is introduced by opening lines followed by a supplication formula.</note>
                     <note>- Each “Postscript” contains the information about the place and date of origin for the relative Gospel:</note>
                     <note>the Gospel of Matthew, Mark and John have the መልአ (መልአት)-type, Luke has ተፈጸመ (ተፈጸመት)-type (about this, cp. Zuurmond 1989, 29-30);</note>
                     <note>in the Postscript for John, the second part with the date on fol. 307va has been erased and probably a second time rewritten on fol. 307vb.</note>
                  </msItem>
